('ad4328c7-f9e5-496c-b492-3216a2893413', 'Introduction to Embedded Systems', 'Embedded systems are used in a wide range of applications, including consumer electronics, medical devices, automotive systems, industrial control systems, and aerospace systems. They typically have limited resources in terms of processing power, memory, and energy consumption, and must operate reliably in real-time environments.', '2023-04-28 04:29:46', '2023-04-28 04:29:46', '019cfe13-ee98-4071-82f8-4f90ca9ec54c'),
('b3dfe711-8a57-4800-a9d9-95f31c025526', 'What is HPC?', 'HPC systems also rely on specialized software tools and programming models that allow developers to take full advantage of the parallel processing capabilities of these systems. These tools include programming languages like MPI, OpenMP, and CUDA, which are designed to facilitate the development of parallel algorithms and applications.', '2023-04-26 04:18:49', '2023-04-26 04:18:49', 'a72d26e5-c36d-4351-993e-43491a3ad017'),
('b58c478d-0f1b-4de4-af9b-7c90230d0bfa', 'Introduction to Computational Biology', 'Computational biology is a field of study that combines computer science, mathematics, and statistics with biological research to analyze and understand biological systems. It involves the development and application of computational methods to analyze large datasets generated from biological experiments and to model biological systems.\n\nThe field of computational biology encompasses a wide range of topics, including genomics, proteomics, transcriptomics, and metabolomics. It also includes the analysis of biological networks, such as metabolic pathways and gene regulatory networks, and the development of computational models to predict the behavior of biological systems.\n\nOne of the key challenges in computational biology is the management and analysis of large datasets. Biological experiments can generate vast amounts of data, and computational methods are needed to extract meaningful information from this data. This requires the use of specialized algorithms and software tools that can handle large datasets and perform complex analyses.', '2023-04-28 04:48:22', '2023-04-28 04:48:22', '4269af63-06ba-48a8-9e50-c96743af6ad9'),
('c596320b-0263-4951-b85b-5483fea59714', 'Vue Step Two', 'Reactive data binding: Vue.js provides a simple and efficient way to bind data to the DOM, allowing you to create dynamic and responsive user interfaces.\n\nComponent-based architecture: Vue.js allows you to break your application down into reusable components, making it easier to manage and scale your codebase.\n\nDirectives: Vue.js provides built-in directives that allow you to add dynamic behavior to your components, such as conditional rendering, event handling, and more.\n\nTemplates: Vue.js provides a simple and powerful template syntax that allows you to declaratively render your components and data.\n\nVirtual DOM: Vue.js uses a virtual DOM to efficiently update the UI when the data changes, making it faster and more efficient than traditional two-way data binding.\n\nRouting: Vue.js has built-in routing capabilities, allowing you to easily create single-page applications with multiple views and routes.\n\nVuex: Vuex is a state management library for Vue.js that provides a centralized store for managing the state of your application.\n\nOverall, Vue.js is a lightweight and flexible framework that makes it easy to build dynamic and interactive user interfaces. It provides many powerful features out-of-the-box, while still being flexible enough to allow for customization and extension as needed.', '2023-05-02 12:20:25', '2023-05-02 12:20:25', '2ed99fff-e742-4a26-b840-c2a7248f351a'),
('c7204622-723b-48eb-b6c4-2dc1b54de713', 'Introduction to Data Analytics and Business Intelligence', 'Data analytics refers to the process of examining large and complex data sets to identify patterns, trends, and insights that can help businesses make data-driven decisions. This involves collecting, cleaning, processing, and analyzing data using statistical and computational techniques to extract useful information.\n\nBusiness intelligence, on the other hand, refers to the tools, technologies, and strategies that businesses use to collect, analyze, and visualize data to gain insights and make informed decisions. This can include dashboards, reports, data warehouses, and other tools that help businesses manage and use data effectively.', '2023-05-02 04:12:58', '2023-05-02 04:12:58', 'a72d26e5-c36d-4351-993e-43491a3ad017'),
('d7cd8fde-bcf3-4fb4-b148-146c264d90cd', 'Introduction to Software Design', 'Software design is the process of creating a plan or blueprint for a software system or application that meets the requirements of users, stakeholders, and customers. It involves translating the software requirements into a detailed design that specifies how the software will be structured, organized, and implemented.', '2023-04-05 06:59:19', '2023-04-05 06:59:19', '2ed99fff-e742-4a26-b840-c2a7248f351a'),
